method.description:
Sets the [Callable] for customizing whether file events are filtered out.
[param filter] needs to return a [bool] value to determine whether to filter out events for the file, and also needs to accept the following arguments in order:
[code skip-lint]int[/code]: The watch ID of the directory manually added by [method FileWatcher.add_watch];
[code skip-lint]String[/code]: The base directory path of the file or directory to be filtered;
[code skip-lint]String[/code]: The file or directory's name to be filtered;
[code skip-lint]int[/code]: A bitmask of [enum FileTypeFlags] indicating the type of the file or directory.
[b]Note:[/b] This callback will be called in a separate thread, so please ensure thread safety.

Sets the [Callable] to listen for and handle file actions.
[param handler] needs to accept the following arguments in order:
[code skip-lint]int[/code]: The watch ID of the directory manually added by [method FileWatcher.add_watch];
[code skip-lint]String[/code]: The path to the parent directory of the file or directory that generated the file action;
[code skip-lint]String[/code]: The filename of the file or directory that generated the file action;
[code skip-lint]int[/code]: A bitmask of [enum FileTypeFlags] indicating the type of the file or directory;
[code skip-lint]int[/code]: The [enum FileAction] that was performed;
[code skip-lint]String[/code]: The old path of the file or directory moved.
[b]Note:[/b] This callback will be called in a separate thread, so please ensure thread safety.
